messages.message:
This is from FRB:
> our developers are asking for Instabase “Flows” --- which I suppose are your files to help the OCR recognize W2, driver’s licenses or other common data types.  Can you please prioritize this request?
iirc we do have some of these things, right?
idk about driver’s licenses, but it feels like there’s been some conversation around w2 and top 4 or 5 paystub providers
Yes we do have the top 5 US paystub providers and W2s
Drivers licenses would be something that @Ted would have the most context on I believe
fwiw, definitely only want to send things we already have
Yeah we don’t have any pre-prepared flows for Drivers Licenses
@Matt has the spreadsheet we sent to Goldman re: the fields we extract for paystub and W2 let me share it with you

Depending on the OCR results on their own data, they could def write some though.

• If the OCR results are good, Refiner or Table Refiner are the best option
• If the OCR results are bad, Visual Refiner is the best option (Visual Refiner is really a custom OCR pipeline)

On top of that, we currently have two efforts to put a deep learning OCR model into Instabase w/in the next few months.
And when that goes production, then we should expect that quality will go up to the point where things like DLs become easily refinable
> we currently have two efforts to put a deep learning OCR model into Instabase w/in the next few months
Just shared the list with you Paul
@dlluncor thank you sir, I see it!
